<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-263-944  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 263 944.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  March 5 1990 v218 n10 p11(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI seeks audit of RHC lobbying. (MCI Communications Corp.;andO;regional holding companies)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mason, Charles.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MCI Communications Corp asks the Federal Communications Commission(FCC) to investigate the possibility that access charges beingpaid to the Bell regional holding companies are being used tofinance a lobbying effort aimed at removing restrictions imposedon the 'Baby Bells' by the Modified Final Judgment.andP;  Such usewould be a violation of FCC regulations, but MCI charges thatinformation currently supplied by the Bells is insufficient toallow the public to determine the origin of such funds.andP;  In itspetition, MCI cites findings by the Massachusetts Public UtilitiesCommission that New England Telephone has improperly includinglobbying and public relations expenses in its rate base.andP;  Therequest for an investigation comes as the FCC prepares to addressseveral issues that impact local exchange carriers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (investigations).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     United States. Federal Communications CommissionBell Regional Holding CompaniesTelecommunicationsTelephone companies.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>